@startuml timestamp-utc-serialization
' Requirements: L1-API-002, L2-API-005
' Source: docs/specs/application-programming-interface/L1.md, docs/specs/application-programming-interface/L2.md
title Timestamp serialization - UTC ISO 8601 / RFC 3339 on every response
autonumber

actor "Operator Client" as Client
participant "HTTP API" as Http
participant "Route Handler" as Handler
participant "Wire Serializer" as Ser
participant "Rfc3339TimestampConverter" as Conv

Client -> Http ++ : GET <any endpoint whose\nresponse contains time fields>
Http -> Handler ++ : dispatch
Handler --> Http -- : response DTO with\nDateTimeOffset fields\n(generationTime, missionTime, ...)
Http -> Ser ++ : Serialize(response DTO)
loop for each time-valued field
  Ser -> Conv ++ : Write(DateTimeOffset value)
  Conv -> Conv : normalize to UTC
  Conv --> Ser -- : "2026-07-17T12:00:00.000Z"
end
note right of Conv
  GIVEN any response containing time fields
  WHEN the payload is serialized
  THEN timestamp strings are
  UTC ISO 8601 / RFC 3339 (L2-API-005);
  applies uniformly to HTTP and
  WebSocket JSON payloads (L1-API-002)
end note
Ser --> Http -- : JSON body with RFC 3339\nUTC timestamp strings
Http --> Client -- : 200 OK
@enduml
